_	Susan Davidson, in her review of the Arena Stage production for "CurtainUp", noted: "...it helps to suspend the disbelief that sullen, anti-social teenagers can change quickly.
_	Informed by the events of the first Gulf War, the Cuban Missile Crisis and the Soviet invasion of Prague, the intent was to recreate these moments when "the world held its breath" and the emotional core of the conflict was the disbelief that the situation could have occurred at all, and the desperation to find a way to bring it to an end.
_	The battle between "Sydney" and "Kormoran" is seen as controversial: the disbelief that a modified merchant ship could so successfully defeat a cruiser combined with the lack of Australian survivors led some to believe that the German account was false.
